I want to thank Glenn for implementing my patch to the keys() method.   But in the process of doing so, a minor new bug was introduced.

The patch contains a line of the form:
   if (rst != null) {
which was changed to
   if (rst != null && rst.next()) {
When we hit the while(rst.next()) loop, the first record will be skipped.

Perhaps that should be,
   if (rst != null && !rst.isAfterLast()) {
instead?
